42:38.560 --> 42:40.400
Thank you, my love. Thank you.

42:40.600 --> 42:42.160
Thank you, guys. Thank you.

42:42.840 --> 42:44.240
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

42:44.320 --> 42:46.320
And then a second toast
to the family:

42:46.400 --> 42:48.600
Margaret, Martha, Clay, everybody else.

42:49.160 --> 42:50.840
You guys just took this so well.

42:51.520 --> 42:53.400
You were in there.
You were suffering,

42:53.480 --> 42:56.600
but there’s a lot of emotional anguish
and mental anguish that we have too.

42:57.120 --> 43:00.840
And you guys were just incredible,
your emotional spirits,

43:01.160 --> 43:02.880
they never wavered, so cheers...

43:02.960 --> 43:04.880
- to you guys.
- La familia!

43:04.960 --> 43:07.080
- La familia!
-

43:07.160 --> 43:08.880
Hear, hear. Santé.

43:08.960 --> 43:09.880
Ching, ching!

43:10.000 --> 43:12.440
- Santé.
- Santé, santé.

43:43.640 --> 43:46.520
I can’t share my experience
for the last eight years

43:47.160 --> 43:48.360
with anybody.

43:48.480 --> 43:51.240
They wouldn’t understand it.
They have no way of knowing

43:51.560 --> 43:53.760
what that means.
I could say, "Well,

43:53.960 --> 43:56.840
I was locked away for eight years
and I didn’t have any privacy

43:56.920 --> 43:59.560
or any freedom.
I was in prison for eight years."

43:59.720 --> 44:03.000
People could say, "You were in prison for
eight years, it must have been terrible!"

44:03.240 --> 44:05.720
And you think, "Yeah it was."

44:05.800 --> 44:10.560
But you have
no real understanding of that.

44:10.680 --> 44:13.000
And I can’t tell you that.

44:13.080 --> 44:16.400
No matter what I tell you
can make you understand and realize that.

44:16.480 --> 44:21.360
And so, therefore you just...
your world is very different

44:21.680 --> 44:23.520
from everybody else’s world.

44:24.640 --> 44:27.120
I wanted to come back to who I was.

44:28.160 --> 44:29.360
But I can't.

44:29.800 --> 44:34.120
So, I’m still working about me

44:34.480 --> 44:37.240
in this world out there.

44:37.520 --> 44:41.840
Then with the realization also,
"Oh, don’t ever forget, Mike,

44:41.920 --> 44:43.760
they're trying to send you back there.

44:43.840 --> 44:47.600
They still think that you’re guilty,
many of them.

44:47.680 --> 44:49.840
They want you go to back there
for the rest of your life.

44:49.920 --> 44:51.400
They want you to die in prison."

44:51.480 --> 44:55.480
So, while you’re trying to move along,

44:55.560 --> 44:57.720
always on your shoulder is this...

44:59.560 --> 45:02.840
heavy burden.
Or, in my case, on my foot,

45:02.960 --> 45:05.240
the monitoring device.

45:05.520 --> 45:07.160
- David!
- How are you, sir?

45:07.240 --> 45:09.320
Good. Fine, fine. I'm fine.

45:09.400 --> 45:11.040
Have you shrunk a little?

45:11.120 --> 45:13.880
I’m still taller than you are.
I don’t care how damn much I’ve shrank!

45:16.160 --> 45:17.520
You look better than
the last time.

45:17.600 --> 45:20.880
Well, shit! If I was worse,
I’d be up there in Maplewood!

45:21.280 --> 45:24.680
Nothing much is gonna happen
in your case, no matter what,

45:25.200 --> 45:27.200
for the rest of this year.

45:27.720 --> 45:29.640
Um, after that,

45:29.760 --> 45:33.960
depending on what
the Attorney General’s office decides,

45:34.040 --> 45:36.080
what the Court of Appeals decides,

45:36.160 --> 45:37.720
- we could be back in...
- Right.

45:37.800 --> 45:41.080
putting it on the docket for trial
sometime next year.

45:42.200 --> 45:44.520
And then of course, the question becomes,

45:45.000 --> 45:47.120
do you want to retry this case,

45:47.400 --> 45:52.040
or do you want to see
if some sort of a resolution

45:52.120 --> 45:55.600
can be negotiated, and there’s
lots of different ways to do that.

45:55.680 --> 45:58.640
So, there’s a no-contest plea,
where you simply are

45:58.720 --> 46:00.840
saying, "I’m not gonna contest this."

46:00.920 --> 46:04.200
There’s an Alford plea,
where you basically say,

46:04.280 --> 46:06.200
"I’m pleading guilty,

46:06.280 --> 46:08.840
but I’m not pleading guilty
because I’m guilty.

46:08.920 --> 46:11.840
I’m pleading guilty because I don’t want
to go through another trial."

46:11.920 --> 46:13.920
I know guys in prison
who have taken an Alford Plea

46:14.000 --> 46:16.560
and said, basically,

46:16.640 --> 46:18.560
"Fuck it. I don’t want to go on
any further."

46:18.640 --> 46:20.760
- Yeah.
- "Just end this damn thing right now."

46:20.840 --> 46:23.080
But what that means is you’re guilty.

46:23.280 --> 46:25.240
- I mean, on the record...
- On the record.

46:25.320 --> 46:27.400
- you're guilty.
- On the record you're guilty.

46:27.480 --> 46:29.640
- I’m not guilty.

46:29.720 --> 46:31.400
I don’t care about any money,
I don’t care... whatever.

46:31.480 --> 46:33.800
I mean, I’m gonna go along
with what you say on this.

46:33.880 --> 46:36.120
Could the DA decide

46:36.200 --> 46:38.360
that he’s just gonna drop it?
He could...

46:38.440 --> 46:40.640
but I don’t think he’s gonna do that.

46:40.720 --> 46:41.640
So...

46:41.960 --> 46:44.400
realistically speaking,
the only three options

46:44.480 --> 46:48.200
are a No Contest Plea,
an Alford Plea, or go to trial.

46:48.280 --> 46:50.320
Even going to trial
doesn’t guarantee innocence.

46:50.400 --> 46:52.080
No, I understand,
but it gives me an option.

46:52.160 --> 46:54.160
The other two, there’s no option.

46:54.240 --> 46:55.840
You’re basically guilty.

46:55.920 --> 46:59.520
And you see, the whole thing is, I didn't
do it, so why would I even do this?

46:59.600 --> 47:00.920
- Right.
- Uh...

47:01.240 --> 47:04.960
- But...
- I think, we don’t need to discuss that

47:05.520 --> 47:07.160
today. I mean...

47:07.240 --> 47:08.600
But nothing's going to be until...

47:08.720 --> 47:10.680
- Oh, it's gonna be...
- ...maybe in the middle of next year.

47:10.760 --> 47:12.680
- At least.
- At least?

47:12.760 --> 47:14.240
Nothing’s gonna happen quickly here.

47:14.320 --> 47:16.520
Jesus. Okay. Alright.

47:40.640 --> 47:43.840
I can remember,
oh, when I was a very young man,

47:43.920 --> 47:48.280
I thought, "I’m going to live a life
with as few regrets as possible."

47:48.800 --> 47:51.920
And now I’m getting to be
a pretty old man.

47:52.280 --> 47:55.920
And I look back and,
oh, Lord, there are some regrets.

47:56.000 --> 47:58.400
"Oh, I wish that...
I wish I had done that differently.

47:58.480 --> 48:02.400
I wish I hadn’t done that. I wish..."
Yes, it’s filled with regrets,

48:03.080 --> 48:09.600
but in the balance I’ve got these
wonderful children.

48:10.560 --> 48:13.480
I had a wonderful relationship
with Kathleen.

48:13.560 --> 48:16.240
I was loved and I loved.

48:17.240 --> 48:19.720
And I still do. And I guess...

48:20.560 --> 48:23.000
that’s about the best you can say
about a person.

48:24.880 --> 48:28.000
Their capacity to love, and mine is...

48:28.160 --> 48:29.160
is infinite.

48:29.240 --> 48:32.200
Honestly, it gets bigger all the time.

48:32.720 --> 48:35.360
And I can look at my children and think,

48:35.680 --> 48:37.480
"Yeah, they love me."

48:39.280 --> 48:40.640
What else do you want?

50:02.400 --> 50:03.600
Did you plant the roses?

50:03.680 --> 50:06.040
No, I didn’t. No. No, no.

50:08.360 --> 50:09.280
Ow.

50:11.040 --> 50:12.200
I can get this one.

50:12.280 --> 50:13.240
Okay.

50:13.640 --> 50:14.480
Here.

50:36.960 --> 50:38.240
Hm.

50:50.560 --> 50:51.480
Ten years later.

50:53.040 --> 50:53.880
I know.

50:57.000 --> 50:58.960
Still hurts.

50:59.400 --> 51:01.400
It’ll always hurt. It’ll never go away.

51:02.080 --> 51:04.440
Ever. None of it ever goes away.

51:07.040 --> 51:08.320
You never forget it.

51:10.920 --> 51:12.400
Always pain, always pain.

